gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 109, Clippers 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Clippers, 109-105. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 33 points, nine rebounds, and six assists as Karl-Anthony Towns (17 points, six rebounds, five assists) and Rudy Gobert (15 points, 18 rebounds) totaled 32 points. Kawhi Leonard (26 points, nine rebounds, four assists), Norman Powell (24 points, 6-9 3PT), and Paul George (16 points, four rebounds, three assists) led Los Angeles as Russell Westbrook totaled 12 points, eight rebounds, and 13 assists in the loss. Minnesota snaps a three-game win streak for the Clippers to improve to 28-11 as the Clippers move to 25-14.
